OL,3,CIs it time for outdated parliamentary
OL,4,Clanguage to 'give way'?
OL,6,FThe use of confusing parliamentary
OL,7,Fjargon in the House of Commons could
OL,8,Fsoon be over.
OL,10,FParliament's Modernisation Committee
OL,11,Fhas recognised that much of the
OL,12,Flanguage used by MPs and Lords is
OL,13,Foutdated and could be made more
OL,14,Faccessible.
OL,16,FIt has set up an inquiry and is taking
OL,17,Fevidence on whether the language used
OL,18,Fin the chamber should be modernised.
