OL,3,CIs it time for outdated parliamentary
OL,4,Clanguage to 'give way'?
OL,6,FThere are dozens of terms used in
OL,7,FParliament that most people would not
OL,8,Funderstand and the committee wants to
OL,9,Fknow if "changes to language could
OL,10,Fmake it easier to understand how
OL,11,FParliament works".
OL,13,FThe British Parliament is one of the
OL,14,Fworld's oldest and a wide range of
OL,15,Funusual traditions have developed in
OL,16,Fits approximately 800-year history.
OL,18,FAmongst language which baffles the
OL,19,Fpublic is the ban on using members'
OL,20,Fnames in the chamber.
